Key Match Events: Travis Head scored a stunning 59 runs off just 23 deliveries against England.
Tim David made an impressive catch to dismiss Jordan Cox.
Jacob Bethell was bowled by Adam Zampa after scoring just two runs.
Liam Livingstone top scored for England with 37 runs off 27 balls.
Sam Curran conceded 30 runs in an over bowled to Travis Head.
Saqib Mahmood removed Travis Head with the last ball of the powerplay.
Adil Rashid bowled Mitchell Marsh for two runs.
Liam Livingstone overturned two lbw shouts to dismiss Matthew Short and Tim David.
Jofra Archer and Saqib Mahmood each took two wickets with yorkers.
Phil Salt was caught at mid-off from the first ball of the chase but was saved by a no-ball call.
Will Jacks was dismissed by Josh Hazlewood.
Phil Salt was caught on the deep backward square boundary for 20 off Sean Abbott.
Pre-Game Insights: England's white-ball reset began with Marcus Trescothick as the temporary coach and Phil Salt as the temporary captain.
This was England's first limited-overs game since the announcement that Brendon McCullum would unite the red- and white-ball coaching roles early next year.
Post-Match Reflections: Phil Salt acknowledged Australia's aggressive start and mentioned that England kept losing wickets at bad times.
Phil Salt insisted that Sam Curran had the potential to be a world-class all-rounder but noted he is not there yet.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Hampshire switched on over 1,000 solar panels before play in their bid to become the world’s greenest cricket club.
